On Wed, 21 Sep 2005, Nemo, the Bus Captain wrote:

> AS you guys know, I'm all about the tire and oil
> FARTS.  However, I still don't have this worked
> out in my head.  If 10W30, 5W30, or 0W30 act the
> same as SAE30 at operating temp--which of course
> is almost all the time you have your engine
> running-- why is there a rush to lower viscosity
> base oil in the name of fuel economy?

Because the hot number used to be "40", but now it is 30 or 20.  The cold
number gets correspondingly lower to improve mileage during warmup, which
is a significant portion of most vehicles' driving cycles.

George
